                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363 Manchuria/299: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-06-12T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 12, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. Your 135, May 24, 6 p.m. The Department concurs in the view expressed in
                    paragraph 2 of your telegram. You are authorized to proceed in the manner and
                    under the conditions set forth in the Department’s 64, April 22, 2 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
